      "type": "ApplicabilityConstraint",
      "name": "COU1 Applicability Constraint — FDA Generic Centrifugal Blood Pump, CPB Duty",
      "description": "The model is applicable only to the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump geometry operating in steady-state CPB duty (continuous flow, non-pulsatile). The applicability domain is restricted to Newtonian blood surrogate (32% glycerol-water, viscosity 0.0035 Pa·s), hematocrit 33–40%, temperature 35–38 °C, and absence of cavitation (inlet pressure > 10 mmHg absolute). Results are not transferable to pulsatile VAD duty or to pumps with substantially different impeller specific-speed (Ns < 800 or Ns > 2200 rpm·(L/min)^0.5·m^-0.75)."
    },
