    "actor": "https://uofa.net/morrison/org/fda-cdrh-cbp-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 ASME V&V 40 credibility factors have been assessed and all achieve levels meeting or exceeding the required levels for Model Risk Level 2. The CFD model demonstrates: (1) correct numerical implementation via benchmark verification; (2) adequate discretisation with GCI_fine = 4.2%; (3) validated hemolysis predictions within 7.3% mean error against in vitro data at all 5 COU operating points; (4) complete uncertainty quantification showing RH < 1 is maintained even at upper uncertainty bounds; (5) sensitivity analysis confirming robustness of worst-case identification to manufacturing tolerances. The validation activities are directly relevant to the COU geometry and operating envelope. No credibility factor shortfalls exist. The model is accepted for use in identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device regulatory submission.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z"
  },
